27/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The education ministry and the inter-university council reached an agreement Sunday (26 October) on a draft bill to reform higher education without resorting to constitutional changes. Education Minister Huseyin Celik expressed satisfaction with the agreement and said such co-operation should continue, as both sides agree Turkey's higher education system requires thorough change.
In other news, Turkish security forces captured 98 illegal immigrants in Istanbul on Sunday. Officials say they will be sent home to Pakistan and India after legal proceedings. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 26/10/03)
